cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with the problem of navigational voice queries posed against an entertainment system, which involves natural language processing and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and user interfaces (HC), which are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with a large dataset and uses neural networks, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) respectively.
